A pregnant cashier at the Ketu/Ikorodu branch of Access Bank affected by the bank’s mass retrenchment of staff, collapsed on Saturday after hearing of her dismissal, SaharaReporters reports. The cashier simply identified as Taiwo, is about three months pregnant. Recall that the bank had announced plans to sack its workers as a result of the negative impact of the Coronavirus outbreak. It was gathered that many of the bank’s staff received their sack letters via email over the weekend with shock and grief. A colleague of the lady, who collapsed, spoke with SaharaReporters on the phone. He said, “Her name is Taiwo. When she got the news today, she collapsed. There were two of them affected by the mass retrenchment from Ketu/Ikorodu Road branch, as of now. We will get to know more on Monday about others who were affected. READ ALSO  Boris Johnson And Fiancee Names Son Taiwo  is about three months pregnant. “When she heard the news, she collapsed. It was friends and family around her that rushed her to the hospital.”